.TH "vc_translate_unicode" 9 "vc_translate_unicode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vc_translate_unicode \- - Combine UTF-8 into Unicode in @vc_utf_char
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vc_translate_unicode
.BI "(struct vc_data *vc "  ","
.BI "int c "  ","
.BI "bool *rescan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vc" 12
virtual console
.IP "c" 12
character to translate
.IP "rescan" 12
we return true if we need more (continuation) data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIvc_utf_char\fP is the being-constructed unicode character.
\fIvc_utf_count\fP is the number of continuation bytes still expected to arrive.
\fIvc_npar\fP is the number of continuation bytes arrived so far.
